qas.question: The Rajpath was constructed similarly to what famous Parisian street?

On what boulevard does the Republic Day parade take place each year?
What annual parade takes place on the Rajpath each January?

context: <a1_0><a2_0>The Rajpath<a2_0/><a1_0/> which was built similar to <a0_0>the Champs-Élysées<a0_0/> in Paris is the ceremonial boulevard for the Republic of India located in New Delhi. The annual <a3_0>Republic Day parade<a3_0/> takes place here on <a4_0>26 January<a4_0/>.
